    Written by BAFTA award-winning writer Kay Mellor (Fat Friends;
    Band Of Gold), The Syndicate is a poignant drama about a group
    of supermarket workers whose lives are turned upside down when
    they win big on the lottery.

    Threatened by the prospect of closure and redundancy, five
    employees of a local Right Buy U are shocked to learn they
    have hit the jackpot. As wild celebrations and spending sprees
    ensue, reality quickly sinks in when new troubles surface for
    the winners.
